caption: This had to be the worst Jamaican food I’ve ever tasted!!! The curry goat appears to be cooked in a crockpot, no flavor, the rice and peas looked white/ colorless  and was flavorless. The rum cake is not a rum cake, omg what the hell?? The beef patty wasn’t bad but no I was so disappointed!!! At least attempt a real rum cake! 0 stars
The chicken soup warms your soul. The jerk chicken was so flavorful and the beef patty was so flaky! Can’t wait to come here again!

I love this place... I drive 45 minutes pass several Jamaican eateries to go here... closest thing to back home...

The price point is amazing and the jerk wings were so flavored, tender, with the just the right amount of spicy heat. The coco bread was okay, but the curry chicken was a big NO! I mean it was DRY even though I asked for extra sauce, unseasoned, and the rice & peas tasted as if it was a few days old. I'll try them again if I'm in their neighborhood but only for the jerk.

My first time today and I Absolutely loved them!!! One of the best Jamaican food spots I've ever had!!! I work in DC and live in Baltimore...I stopped on the way home and got dinner for my kids since it was so good and they loved it too!!!

Only three stars because every time I’m in the mood to get Negril’s food, I know I have to deal with the negative vibes of the FOH employees. So... yep. THESE STARS ARE FOR THE FOOD ONLY!!

THIS PLACE IS NASTY.  AND THE TERRIBLE CUSTOMER SERVICE IS A CHERRY TO TOP IT OFF.  DESERVES AN EPISODE IN KITCHEN NIGHTMARES.  First of all, the spice distribution is off. They use too much Tumeric. Secondly, the food tastes watery, instead of a developed broth for their curry,  it taste like they use water and just season it with some subpar curry powder.  And there is so much filling. If I wanted just curry chicken, I would have ordered that. I'm so dissappointed, because I always see people leaving that establishment. I won't be there again.

This restaurant is my preferable site.  Of all restaurants I know I prefere it most. I always suggests to my friends to go to visit this place. Whenever  I want to go to a decent meal, this is the place that comes first to my mind.  Great and all sorts of  food and a large list of dishes.professional staff members, and pleasant mood. I ordered a large chicken soup from here two days ago. Whomever shared my soup shared it with love, because it has lasted me two days, and it has really helped me while I have been under the weather. The soup is meaty with delicious dumplings and a really good flavor. I am Jamaican, and this is about as close as I can get to my mother’s home cooking while I’m away.I’m very grateful. Thank you.

This was my first visit. I ordered the jerk special, 2 pieces of jerk chicken, rice and cabbage. The chicken (eating now) is EXTREMELY dry. There is nothing "jerk" about it. It really doesn't taste like jerk chicken. There isn't enough jerk seasoning throughout on the chicken. It wasn't hot at all.  Maybe I will try the ox tails or curry but will not be trying the jerk chicken. I've had authentic jerk chicken and this aint it.

I enjoyed my 2nd visit to the DC location. The food was good and hot just like I like it!

I have been in DC for ten years and when I came to Howard I was genuinely happy about some Caribbean Cuisine like my moms home-cooking (my family is from Trinidad and Tortola (BVI). Wellllll this food is not Caribbean cuisine to me, not Jamaican either. I just...don't enjoy the food. If I am to eat here I would get the cocoa bread because you can't go wrong. The cabbage to me is too oily and the curry chicken just doesn't taste like curry chicken to me. Oh they normally have dessert, like cakes and stuff that aren't that bad. I personally just don't enjoy the food. Location is convenient, especially for Howard students. Service isn't that bad. And honestly, they have a good flow of people so I may be in the minority as far as people who don't like their food. I gave it two starts because I do go grab rice and gravy when I am starving, and my boss loves their coco bread and beef patty. But if i wanted West Indian food, I personally would not go here.

Negril is a staple of Howard University's culinary options. It is a Jamaican restaurant that serves jerk chicken, ox tail, beef patties, rum cake and most important of all, Coco Bread. Since leaving Howard it has been extremely difficult finding Coco Bread at any Caribbean location. This restaurant singlehandedly changed my desired planetary habits. They have reasonable prices are strive to provide quick service. However, around lunch time the lines can get long.
